From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Subject: [PATCH] Initialize TransactionContext invalidation policy

Valgrind reports "conditional jump or move depends on uninitialised
value(s)" in ClientContext::ErrorInvalidatesTransaction because
TransactionContext::invalidation_policy is never initialized: the
constructor's initializer list only sets context, auto_commit and
current_transaction, leaving invalidation_policy (and auto_rollback)
with indeterminate values. GetInvalidationPolicy() then reads the
uninitialized member, and the taint propagates through Prepare,
TryBindRelation and ExecuteTaskInternal.

Give both members default initializers matching the defaults used by
the TransactionInfo constructor.

See https://www.stats.ox.ac.uk/pub/bdr/memtests/valgrind/duckdb/
---
 .../duckdb/transaction/transaction_context.hpp           | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/duckdb/src/include/duckdb/transaction/transaction_context.hpp b/src/duckdb/src/include/duckdb/transaction/transaction_context.hpp
--- a/src/duckdb/src/include/duckdb/transaction/transaction_context.hpp
+++ b/src/duckdb/src/include/duckdb/transaction/transaction_context.hpp
@@ -72,8 +72,8 @@ public:
 private:
 	ClientContext &context;
 	bool auto_commit;
-	TransactionInvalidationPolicy invalidation_policy;
-	bool auto_rollback;
+	TransactionInvalidationPolicy invalidation_policy = TransactionInvalidationPolicy::STANDARD_POLICY;
+	bool auto_rollback = false;

 	unique_ptr<MetaTransaction> current_transaction;

--
2.52.0
